      • getPicklist

        @GET(value="/app/list/{typeOfProcess}/{username}/{password}")
retrofit2.Call<java.util.List<PickList>> getPicklist(@Path(value="typeOfProcess")
                                                                                                                    java.lang.String typeOfProcess,
                                                                                                                    @Path(value="username")
                                                                                                                    java.lang.String username,
                                                                                                                    @Path(value="password")
                                                                                                                    java.lang.String password)
        Performs the GET request for one of the three list types. Returns a List with PickList objects. The response body holds a List with PickList objects. The List contains PickList objects from the given type of Procedure. The Type of Procedure must either be "S", "M" or "E" for Sanger, Manual or Extra. The List can be empty.
        Parameters:
        username - is not allowed to be null and must not be an empty String ("").
        password - is not allowed to be null and must not be an empty String ("").
        typeOfProcess - must be either "S","M" or "E".
        Returns:
        call object which can be enqueued as request
